      "comment_id" : 27110663,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Yes, but Java documentation says that &quot;This is ordinarily too costly, but may be more efficient than alternatives when traversal operations vastly outnumber mutations, and is useful when you cannot or don&#39;t want to synchronize traversals, yet need to preclude interference among concurrent threads.&quot;"
