    "question_id" : 18448671,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>One alternative method is convert your <code>List</code> to <code>array</code>, iterate them and remove them directly from the <code>List</code> based on your logic.</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; myList = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;(); // You can use either list or set\n\nmyList.add(\"abc\");\nmyList.add(\"abcd\");\nmyList.add(\"abcde\");\nmyList.add(\"abcdef\");\nmyList.add(\"abcdefg\");\n\nObject[] obj = myList.toArray();\n\nfor(Object o:obj)  {\n    if(condition)\n        myList.remove(o.toString());\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
